21 26-51-701. Definitions.
22 As used in this Act, unless the context otherwise requires:
23 (a) “Business income” means income arising from transactions and
24 activity in the regular course of the taxpayer's trade or business and
25 includes income from tangible and intangible property if the acquisition,
26 management, and disposition of the property constitute integral parts of the
27 taxpayer's regular trade or business operations "Apportionable income" means:
